    "body": "### Problem\n\n(Tracking issue, feel free to correct...)\n\n`nvim`, in particular `libnvim`, does not set SONAME. libcurl sets SONAME and they are pretty pleased with themselfs: https://daniel.haxx.se/blog/2024/10/30/eighteen-years-of-abi-stability/\n\nOTOH, I have this old reference in my notes: https://chromium.googlesource.com/external/github.com/DynamoRIO/dynamorio/+/d4c6ad58673789bfc575c456799e192add2c6a02/core/CMakeLists.txt\n\n```\n# We only set the version/soversion on Windows to avoid many negatives\n# (i#1374, i#2127, Android \"adb push\" not supporting symlinks, etc.) and\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSet SONAME version in `libnvim` and maybe also `nvim`.\n\n- set it to API_LEVEL? probably not: changing the SONAME number causes downstream havoc (see the \"libcurl\" post above), thus it should rarely change.\n- presumably using cmake `SOVERSION` https://cmake.org/cmake/help/latest/prop_tgt/SOVERSION.html\n\nThis (old old) patch may help:\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/CMakeLists.txt b/src/nvim/CMakeLists.txt\nindex 928d473b04b8..6cc6120becfc 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/CMakeLists.txt\n+++ b/src/nvim/CMakeLists.txt\n@@ -409,6 +409,11 @@ install_helper(TARGETS nvim)\n \n set_property(TARGET nvim APPEND PROPERTY\n              INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES ${LUA_PREFERRED_INCLUDE_DIRS})\n+set_target_properties(\n+  nvim\n+  PROPERTIES\n+    VERSION 43\n+)\n \n if(ENABLE_LTO AND (POLICY CMP0069))\n   include(CheckIPOSupported)\n@@ -493,10 +498,22 @@ add_library(\n )\n set_property(TARGET libnvim APPEND PROPERTY\n              INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES ${LUA_PREFERRED_INCLUDE_DIRS})\n+  # Static lib (.a, not .so), thus no SOVERSION.\n+  # SOVERSION ${NVIM_API_LEVEL}\n+  #\n+  # make libnvim => build/lib/libnvim.a\n+  #\n+  # verify:\n+  #     readelf -d  /path/to/library.so | grep SONAME\n set_target_properties(\n   libnvim\n   PROPERTIES\n     POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE ON\n+    VERSION 42\n     OUTPUT_NAME nvim\n )\n set_property(\n```",
